jobDescription:
Driven by a high-caliber workforce, Ameresco is a leading clean technology integrator and renewable asset developer, owner and operator. Our comprehensive services include energy efficiency, infrastructure upgrades, asset sustainability and renewable energy solutions throughout North America and Europe. Our renewable energy assets and customer projects have delivered a cumulative carbon offset equivalent to over 60 million metric tons of carbon dioxide since going public in 2010.

Grounded in our C.A.R.I.N.G. values and guided by our Environmental, Social and Governance practices, we are proud of our engaging workplace with a host of competitive benefits and wellness programs. Our teams work collaboratively to deliver best-in-class solutions with a relentless focus on customer satisfaction. In pursuit of energizing a sustainable world, our people and purpose set Ameresco apart.

Help shape the future of energy by working for an award-winning team, honored to be recognized by agencies including Best and Brightest Companies to Work for in the Nation and Forbes for our company culture, industry leadership, and client projects. Ameresco is fueled by a dynamic team that embraces diversity, career development opportunities, and -- most importantly – employees driven by doing well by doing good.

Responsibilities: 

Manage large data sets and provide quality assurance of data management activities;

Provide oversight and guidance to AssetPlanner® clients;

Work with clients to implement the AssetPlanner® software system;

Support data development team with data entry and data analysis for client requests and consulting projects;

Assist with the development of reports and presentations to clients;

Provide software technical support to clients with a professional and courteous manner ;

Provide support and guidance to clients on data analysis and integrity;

Perform data science techniques to query database and provide insights;

Conduct on-line and in-person software training sessions with client;

Test new functions and features before software is released;

Develop User Guide and Training resources; and

Perform Other Duties As Required.

 Minimum Qualifications:

Certificate in Business Intelligence – Data Analysis and Reporting;

Bachelor’s degree in computer sciences or related field, or equivalent work experience;

Minimum 2 years of experience with database administration, data management, data analysis, software implementation and technical support;

Additional Preferred Qualifications:

Experience with Microsoft office and expertise with Microsoft access and Microsoft excel;

Familiarity with Asset Management and building sciences is a bonus.

Experience with large datasets and data repositories;

Experience working with building/asset management software systems or Enterprise Asset Management (EAM) systems.

Excellent communication skills for working with clients; highly organized; attentive to detail; professional and courteous demeanor; proven organizational, planning, facilitation, customer service and management skills.

Ameresco Canada Inc. is committed to providing accommodations for applicants with disabilities. If you require an accommodation, we will work with you to meet your needs.
